      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.7243" xml:lang="it">
        <pb n="1"/>
        <dateline>Roma, Via Condotti 75.<lb/> 2 giugno 1908. </dateline>
        <opener>Carissimo Amico e Collega,</opener>
        <p>La soscrizione per la fondazione Ascoli<note n="1" place="foot"
              type="editorial">Die Idee zu dieser Stiftung nach dem Vorbild der <ref
              target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.321">Diez-Stiftung</ref> wurde im Jahr 1907 von der <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.4459">
              <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Società filologica romana</hi>

            </ref> gefasst.</note> resterà ancora aperta per un anno circa. Non occorre dunque che Ella si dia fretta per ciò. Del resto, da Lei, più che il concorso pecuniario, se desidererebbe – ove Le se ne porgesse occasione – un appoggio morale. Nei paesi della Germania poco o nulla si sa di questa fondazione che mira ad istituire un premio <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">internazionale</hi>.<note n="2" place="foot"
              type="editorial">Ein Hinweis auf diese Stiftung findet sich z.B. in <hi rend="unknown"
              rendition="#none">Modern Language Notes</hi> XXII, 2, 1907, 64: „FONDAZIONE ASCOLI. To the Editors of Mod. Lang. Notes. SIRS: - Some of your readers will be interested to learn that through the initiative of the Società Filologica Romana a fund is being raised in memory of the late Graziadio Ascoli, from which prizes are to be awarded periodically to the authors of works in Romance philology or in some branch of it. It is proposed to have the contest international, and accordingly it is hoped that contributions will be made by persons or societies in all countries. The latest report which I have seen (Studj Romanzi, V, 1907, pp. 323-325), gives the amount already received as a little less than 5000 lire, much of this sum being in small contributions. The subscription will be closed March 31, 1908; and until that date contributions may be sent tot he Banca d‘Italia, sede di Roma, payable to the bank itself, to be credited to the account of the Fondazione Ascoli. KENNETH McKENZIE Yale University“. – Der zit. Beitrag in den <hi
              rend="unknown"
              rendition="#none">Studj Romanzi</hi> nennt die ersten Stifter. Aus Deutschland, Österreich und der Schweiz finden sich die folgenden Namen: <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1389">
Hermann Diels</persName> (Berlin), <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2782">Edmund Stengel</persName> (Greifswald), <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1830">Antonio Ive</persName> (Graz), <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2581">Karl Eduard Sachau</persName> (Berlin), <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2987">Gustav Weigand</persName> (Leipzig), <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.4458">Berthold Wiese</persName> (Leipzig) und <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2233">Heinrich Morf</persName> (Frankfurt a. M.).</note> Se Ella volesse dirne o farne dire qualche parola in un giornale tedesco, non dubito che gioverebbe assai alla causa.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Con i migliori augurj e saluti</salute>
          <lb/>
          <salute>il Suo aff<hi rendition="#sup">mo</hi>
          </salute>
          <lb/>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2219">EMonaci</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
